verses.text:
Lord, I have made thy word my choice, My hope, my chief delight;
From read thy law from day to day, Let not my heart depart;
From read thy law from day to day, Let not my heart depart.

I'll meditate thine in-tent law, Before the early dawn;
And when the labor of the day Is o'er, I'll read thy word;
And when the labor of the day Is o'er, I'll read thy word.

The mercy they'll be lifted, That sat me right heart above;
Till mortal life shall close in death, And I shall see my God;
Till mortal life shall close in death, And I shall see my God.
